  "response": "For NEET preparation, while NCERT is an excellent fundamental resource, it may not be completely sufficient for organic chemistry. Here are some recommendations:\n\n1. NCERT Benefits:\n- Provides basic concepts\n- Covers important topics\n- Recommended as primary study material\n- Most NEET questions are directly from NCERT\n\n2. Additional Recommendations:\n- Study NCERT thoroughly\n- Refer to additional reference books\n- Practice previous year question papers\n- Take mock tests\n- Solve topic-wise multiple-choice questions\n\n3. Suggested Additional Resources:\n- O.P. Tandon for Organic Chemistry\n- Physical Chemistry by P. Bahadur\n- Organic Chemistry by Morrison and Boyd\n- NEET practice question banks\n- Online video lectures\n\n4. Key Focus Areas:\n- Understand reaction mechanisms\n- Learn named reactions\n- Practice numerical problems\n- Memorize important organic compounds\n- Study isomerism and functional groups\n\n5. Study Strategy:\n- Read NCERT multiple times\n- Make concise notes\n- Practice solving problems\n- Analyze weak areas\n- Regular revision\n\nRemember, while NCERT is crucial, a comprehensive approach combining multiple resources will improve your preparation.",
